docs.abstract: As regulators seek ways to curb the company’s power, there is more focus on the vast index — hundreds of billions of web pages — behind its search engine.
docs.snippet: As regulators seek ways to curb the company’s power, there is more focus on the vast index — hundreds of billions of web pages — behind its search engine.
docs.lead_paragraph: OAKLAND, Calif. — In 2000, just two years after it was founded, Google reached a milestone that would lay the foundation for its dominance over the next 20 years: It became the world’s largest search engine, with an index of more than one billion web pages.

headline.main: Google Dominates Thanks to an Unrivaled View of the Web
headline.print_headline: Google Dominates Thanks to a Vast Index

docs.abstract: The hackers gained more access than the company previously understood, though they were unable to modify code or get into its products and emails.
docs.snippet: The hackers gained more access than the company previously understood, though they were unable to modify code or get into its products and emails.
docs.lead_paragraph: Microsoft said on Thursday that the far-reaching Russian hack of U.S. government agencies and private corporations had gone further into its network than the company previously understood.

headline.main: Microsoft Says Russian Hackers Viewed Some of Its Source Code
headline.print_headline: Microsoft Says Russian Hackers Went Deep Into Systems in Widespread Attack

docs.abstract: One of the richest women in the world devoted decades to preparing for a pandemic.
docs.snippet: One of the richest women in the world devoted decades to preparing for a pandemic.
docs.lead_paragraph: As the valedictorian of her Dallas high school, Melinda Gates delivered a graduation speech that included a quote attributed to Ralph Waldo Emerson. “To know even one life has breathed easier because you have lived,” she told her classmates, “this is to have succeeded.”

headline.main: Why Melinda Gates Spends Time ‘Letting My Heart Break’
headline.print_headline: The Reasons Melinda Gates Spends Time ‘Letting My Heart Break’

docs.abstract: Nearly a decade of hype led to a troubled release riddled with glitches, a livid fan base, refunds for potentially millions of players and a possible class-action lawsuit.
docs.snippet: Nearly a decade of hype led to a troubled release riddled with glitches, a livid fan base, refunds for potentially millions of players and a possible class-action lawsuit.
docs.lead_paragraph: The hype around Cyberpunk 2077 had been building for nearly a decade.

headline.main: Cyberpunk 2077 Was Supposed to Be the Biggest Video Game of the Year. What Happened?
headline.print_headline: Pantsless Motorcyclists: The Story Behind the Cyberpunk Debacle

byline.original: By Mike Isaac and Kellen Browning

docs.abstract: The Salesforce C.E.O.’s planned acquisition of Slack will have him competing directly with the Goliath that is Microsoft.
docs.snippet: The Salesforce C.E.O.’s planned acquisition of Slack will have him competing directly with the Goliath that is Microsoft.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Five years ago, Marc Benioff negotiated to sell Salesforce, the software company he co-founded in 1999 and has run ever since, to Microsoft. If the deal had gone through, he would have been richly rewarded — but, in the end, just another employee of the tech colossus.

headline.main: Marc Benioff Sets His Sights on Microsoft

docs.abstract: Silicon Valley is building a powerful influence industry in Brussels, which has “never seen this kind of money” spent this way.
docs.snippet: Silicon Valley is building a powerful influence industry in Brussels, which has “never seen this kind of money” spent this way.
docs.lead_paragraph: A leaked document jolted the European Union capital of Brussels in October, laying out in painstaking detail plans by Google to undermine new legislation that could severely damage its digital advertising business.

headline.main: Big Tech Turns Its Lobbyists Loose on Europe, Alarming Regulators
headline.print_headline: Big Tech Sets Its Lobbyists Loose on Europe

byline.original: By Adam Satariano and Matina Stevis-Gridneff

docs.abstract: Both Sony and Microsoft, the maker of Xbox, said they would also offer refunds to gamers while the developer of the much-hyped title works to fix bugs and glitches.
docs.snippet: Both Sony and Microsoft, the maker of Xbox, said they would also offer refunds to gamers while the developer of the much-hyped title works to fix bugs and glitches.
docs.lead_paragraph: Sony, the company that owns and operates PlayStation, announced late Thursday that it would offer refunds to people who purchased Cyberpunk 2077 and remove what had been one of the year’s most highly anticipated video games from its online store, after a week of negative reviews and criticism from users over its poor performance.

headline.main: Sony Removes Cyberpunk 2077 From PlayStation Store After Complaints
headline.print_headline: Sony Pulls Cyberpunk 2077 As Negative Reviews Pile Up

docs.abstract: Minutes after the government statement, President-elect Joseph R. Biden Jr. warned that his administration would impose “substantial costs” on those responsible. President Trump has been silent on the hacking.
docs.snippet: Minutes after the government statement, President-elect Joseph R. Biden Jr. warned that his administration would impose “substantial costs” on those responsible. President Trump has been silent on the hacking.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Federal officials issued an urgent warning on Thursday that hackers who American intelligence agencies believed were working for the Kremlin used a far wider variety of tools than previously known to penetrate government systems, and said that the cyberoffensive was “a grave risk to the federal government.”

headline.main: More Hacking Attacks Found as Officials Warn of ‘Grave Risk’ to U.S. Government
headline.print_headline: Range of Tools In a Vast Hack Elevates Fears

byline.original: By David E. Sanger and Nicole Perlroth

docs.abstract: Evidence from the security firm CrowdStrike suggests that companies that sell software on behalf of Microsoft were used to break into Microsoft’s Office 365 customers.
docs.snippet: Evidence from the security firm CrowdStrike suggests that companies that sell software on behalf of Microsoft were used to break into Microsoft’s Office 365 customers.
docs.lead_paragraph: As the United States comes to grips with a far-reaching Russian cyberattack on federal agencies, private corporations and the nation’s infrastructure, new evidence has emerged that the hackers hunted their victims through multiple channels.

headline.main: Russians Are Believed to Have Used Microsoft Resellers in Cyberattacks
